**12.** An Insurer may invest in the “Other Forms of Capital” issued by another Insurer subject to the following: 

   - i. such investments shall only be classified under “Other investments”; 

   - ii. such instruments shall be subject to the exposure norms as specified in IRDAI (Investment) Regulations, 2016 as amended from time to time; 

   - iii. Such investments shall not qualify as an admissible asset for determining the Control Level of Solvency; 

